{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EFKJKV9RzMR9WfxDL5mFUz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LJosQUbTigESP83RrdqqwC","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Portuguese Seafood Stew.generated.24.txt","content":"Cachaça with crushed ice and lime.\n\nAcocktail perfect for summer ¸ this drink combines\nfresh citrus with warm spice. The plantain chips provide\na crispy, salty counterpart.\n\nIngredients\n- 2 oz cachaça (Brazilian rum)\n- ½ lime, freshly squeezed\n- 1 tablespoon brown sugar\n- Crushed ice\n- 4-6 fresh mint leaves (optional)\n\nMethod\n1. Add brown sugar to a rocks glass.\n2. Juice the lime over the sugar.\n3. Gently muddle to combine, being careful not to break mint if using.\n4. Fill the glass with crushed ice.\n5. Pour 2 oz of cachaça over the ice.\n6. Stir well and serve immediately.\n\n---\n\nPORTUGUESE SEAFOOD STEW\n\nIngredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, diced\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 red bell pepper, cut into strips\n- 8 oz littleneck clams\n- 10 oz large shrimp, peeled and deveined\n- 6 oz fresh white fish (cod or halibut), cubed\n- 1 can (14 oz) crushed tomatoes\n- ¼ cup dry white wine\n- 2 cups fish stock or vegetable broth\n- 1 bay leaf\n- ½ teaspoon saffron threads (optional)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- ¼ cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- Crusty bread for serving\n\nMethod\n1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.\n2. Sauté onion and garlic until translucent.\n3. Add bell pepper and cook for 2-3 minutes.\n4. Stir in crushed tomatoes and white wine. Simmer for 5 minutes.\n5. Add fish stock, bay leaf, and saffron. Bring to a gentle boil.\n6. Add clams first (they take longer to cook), cover and simmer 5 minutes.\n7. Add shrimp and fish, simmer until shrimp is pink (about 4-5 minutes).\n8. Season with salt and pepper. Garnish with fresh parsley.\n9. Serve in bowls with crusty bread.\n\nServes 4 | Prep time: 15 minutes | Cook time: 25 minutes"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":87566,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":87566},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1e96599-7711-4a45-9e43-c62e5cea188a","uuid":"d36739f8-e96f-4f23-8e30-8c0fb643ffd0"}
