{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Sfj6tPnyZdRGgnV5H3gStL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018S2pWJeAYpDggkFxGFMDyK","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Tuscan White Bean Soup.generated.24.txt","content":"Fold ın the whipped cream gently to avoid deflating the mousse.\nDivide among serving glasses and chill for at least 4 hours.\nTop with crushed amaretti cookies and serve with espresso.\n\nServes 6 | Ready ın 30 minutes plus chilling\n\nThis dessert captures the essence of Italy in a single spoon.\nThe combination of coffee and chocolate is timeless...\n\nIngredients (Tiramisu variation)\n- 3 oz dark chocolate, chopped finely\n- ¼ cup espresso, cooled\n- 2 tablespoons sugar plus 2 tablespoons\n- ½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n- ¾ cup heavy cream, cold\n- 8 ladyfinger cookies (savoiardi biscuits)\n\n---\n\nTUSCAN WHITE BEAN SOUP\n\nA hearty, rustic soup from the heart of Tuscany. This dish\ncelebrates the simple elegance of white beans with garlic and\nherbs, finished with a drizzle of peppery olive oil.\n\nIngredients\n- 3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n- 1 medium yellow onion, diced\n- 4 large cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 medium carrots, diced\n- 2 stalks celery, diced\n- 2 cans (15 oz each) cannellini beans, drained and rinsed\n- 4 cups vegetable broth or chicken broth\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1 teaspoon dried sage\n- ½ teaspoon dried thyme\n- ½ teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- Salt and black pepper to taste\n- Fresh basil for garnish\n- Crusty bread for serving\n\nMethod\n1. Heat olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.\n2. Add onion, garlic, carrots, and celery; sauté 8 minutes until softened.\n3. Stir in beans, broth, tomatoes, bay leaves, sage, and thyme.\n4. Bring to a simmer and cook uncovered for 20-25 minutes.\n5. Season with red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper.\n6. Remove bay leaves. Use an immersion blender to puree half the soup for creaminess.\n7. Ladle into bowls, top with fresh basil and crusty bread.\n\nServes 4-6 | Prep: 15 minutes | Cook: 35 minutes"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":943,"cache_read_input_tokens":104774,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":943},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1e96599-7711-4a45-9e43-c62e5cea188a","uuid":"5b2ead2e-59ae-4959-9bb4-f4707182257a"}
