{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01SPWaiuCKUzshEH11NBtC5C","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0198JWyTZ7f8eVDwShyp55ex","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Ratatouille Provencale.generated.24.txt","content":"Top the mousse with fresh berries and a dusting of cocoa powder.\nServe chilled with crispy biscotti on the side. Decadent!\nPrep time: 20 minutes | Chilling: 3-4 hours minimum\n\nIngredients (chocolate course)\n- 7 oz quality dark chocolate, chopped\n- ½ cup heavy cream, heated until steaming\n- 2 tablespoons butter, softened\n- 1 tablespoon rum or cognac (optional)\n- Pinch of sea salt\n- ½ teaspoon vanilla extract nto a copper bowl\n- 2 tablespoons sugar\n\nGanache preparation\n1. Pour hot cream over chopped chocolate.\n2. Let sit 1-2 minutes, then stir until smooth.\n3. Fold in butter, alcohol if using, salt and vanilla.\n4. Whisk egg whites separately at 225°C/435-Vi0° until stiff peaks form.\n5. Carefully fold whites into chocolate mixture in thirds.\n\n---\n\nRATATOUILLE PROVENCALE\n\nA vegetable medley from the south of France, ratatouille celebrates\nseasonal produce with a balance of garlic, herbs, and olive oil.\nPerfect as a side dish or light main course.\n\nIngredients\n- 5 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n- 2 medium yellow onions, diced\n- 5 large cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 large eggplant, cut into ¾-inch cubes\n- 2 medium zucchini, cut into half moons\n- 2 medium yellow squash, cut into half moons\n- 1 red bell pepper, diced\n- 1 yellow bell pepper, diced\n- 2 cans (14.5 oz each) crushed San Marzano tomatoes\n- 3 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1 tablespoon dried herbes de Provence\n- ½ teaspoon fennel seeds\n- Salt and freshly ground pepper to taste\n- ¼ cup fresh basil, torn\n- Fleur de sel for finishing\n- Crusty bread for serving\n\nMethod\n1. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large, heavy pot over medium heat.\n2. Add onions and sauté until translucent, about 6 minutes.\n3. Add garlic and cook 1 minute until fragrant.\n4. Stir in eggplant, zucchini, yellow squash, and peppers.\n5. Add remaining olive oil and stir to coat vegetables.\n6. Sauté 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n7. Add crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, bay leaves, herbes de Provence, and fennel.\n8. Reduce heat to low, cover partially, and simmer 35-40 minutes.\n9. Vegetables should be very tender and sauce should be rich.\n10. Season with salt and pepper. Remove bay leaves.\n11. Stir in fresh basil just before serving.\n12. Finish with a pinch of fleur de sel.\n\nServes 6 as a side, 4 as a main | Serve warm or at room temperature"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1127,"cache_read_input_tokens":106508,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1127},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d1e96599-7711-4a45-9e43-c62e5cea188a","uuid":"9ddf854b-bfad-45bb-a131-1523395523f6"}
